\par\plain {\f0\fs24 28-31}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 Now, why was it so important to Jacob that his body be returned to Canaan, the promised land, to be buried with Abraham and Isaac?}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 First, because Jacob believed the great promises of God, the promises that God had made to Abraham and to Isaac and to himself on at least two different occasions. (See outline and notes\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Ge. 28:12\endash 15; 35:9\endash 12.)}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab He believed the promise of }{\f0\fs24\i1 the promised seed}{\f0\fs24 , that Israel would one day become a great nation of people and through Israel God would send the very special seed, the Savior of the world. (See notes\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Ge. 12:2\endash 3; 12:3 for more discussion.)}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab He believed in }{\f0\fs24\i1 the promised land}{\f0\fs24 , that God was going to give the promised land to the people of God, those who believed in the true and living God. (See note\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Ge. 12:1}{\f0\fs24\super c}{\f0\fs24  for more discussion.)}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 Jacob was declaring his faith in these promises by asking for his body to be returned to the promised land.}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge47.28-31&off=990&ctx=he+head+of+his+bed.%0a~Now%2c+why+was+it+so+i"}{\fldrslt\f2\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, p. 383). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24
\par\pard\plain \fi360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 Fourth, the stress that Jacob placed upon his body\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s being returned to the promised land also shows his great faith in the promises of God. Note how he did all that he could to bind Joseph, to make absolutely sure that Joseph followed through with his promise. Jacob demanded that Joseph both take the oath and swear that he would bury his body in the promised land with the other two fathers who had clung to the great promises of God.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24 Fifth, note what Jacob did when Joseph took the oath and swore: he bowed and worshipped God (v. 31}{\f0\fs24\super b}{\f0\fs24 ). Some translations say that he worshipped while leaning upon his staff (}{\f0\fs24\i1 NIV Study Bible}{\f0\fs24 ). The point to see is that he worshipped God, for he knew that his burial would be a great witness to the great promises of God. In fact, this is exactly what Scripture declares:}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab Jacob was acting in faith, faith in God\u8217\'92s great promises.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93By faith Jacob, when he was a dying, blessed both the sons of Joseph; and worshipped, leaning upon the top of his staff\u8221\'94 (He. 11:21)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab Abraham had acted in faith, faith in God\u8217\'92s great promises.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93For he looked for a city which hath foundations, whose builder and maker is God\u8221\'94 (He. 11:10)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob had all acted in faith, faith in God\u8217\'92s great promises.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93These all died in faith, not having received the promises, but having seen them afar off, and were persuaded of them, and embraced them, and confessed that they were strangers and pilgrims on the earth. For they that say such things declare plainly that they seek a country. And truly, if they had been mindful of that country from whence they came out, they might have had opportunity to have returned. But now they desire a better country, that is, an heavenly: wherefore God is not ashamed to be called their God: for he hath prepared for them a city\u8221\'94 (He. 11:13\endash 16).}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge47.28-31&off=5598&ctx=r+more+discussion.)%0a~Fourth%2c+the+stress+t"}{\fldrslt\f2\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, pp. 383\endash 384). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.}
